\DOC pp_word_signed_bin

\TYPE {pp_word_signed_bin : unit -> unit}

\SYNOPSIS
Pretty print words as signed (two's complement) binary numbers.

\EXAMPLE

{
- word4Lib.pp_word_signed_bin();
> val it = () : unit
- ``n2w 12``;
> val it = ``-0b100`` : term
}

\COMMENTS
Only available after running {mkword.exe}.
HOL will fail to parse the pretty printed output.

\SEEALSO
pp_word_unsigned_bin, pp_word_unsigned_oct, pp_word_unsigned_hex,
pp_word_signed_oct, pp_word_signed_dec, pp_word_signed_hex, pp_word_off

\ENDDOC
